{"id":"ev_3cdd675d61d94779","runId":"run_298","type":"delegation","at":1782828710364,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_7cb2133f6bf7472c","atom":0,"task":"TICKET 0087 — Oscar tasking Deb: decision/owner-map-first atom (READ-ONLY investigation + ONE design note; do NOT change product/machinery code in this atom).\n\nBUG: When Oscar tasks Deb for an orchestration/machinery repair via the `request-deb-repair` path, the daemon ALWAYS launches a brand-new headless Deb subprocess, even when a Deb session is already active (visible or hidden) for that workspace. Founder's desired behavior (ticket 0087): if a Deb is already active for the workspace, route the repair to that active Deb instead of spawning a separate headless one.\n\nKnown facts (verify them yourself, don't trust this list):\n- The repair turn is launched via `runRepairDialogueTurn` (packages/daemon/src/launcher.ts ~1787-1807), which unconditionally builds a fresh adapter command with `headless: true` and runs it via `ctx.runHeadless ?? runHeadlessProcess` — a raw OS subprocess that is NEVER registered in the session store or `ctx.liveRefs`.\n- `requestOscarDebRepair` (launcher.ts ~1415-1556) only guards on an active *run* (`ctx.inFlight`); it never checks for an active Deb *session*. The ticket scenario is the post-wrap-but-not-torn-down window (run no longer `running`, so the 409 guard doesn't fire, but the spawnObserver Deb pane is still alive).\n- An active pane Deb (packages/core/src/runner/observer.ts) runs the OBSERVER prompt and communicates via files (deb-status.json / deb-nudge.json / deb-terminal-snapshot.json) — it does NOT speak the repair-dialogue DebRepairResponse JSON contract that the headless turn produces.\n- Live-session-by-persona lookups already exist for Oscar at launcher.ts ~1384 and ~2739; but session tracking is run-scoped (`store.listSessions(runId)`), NOT workspace-keyed. Oz sessions are workspace-keyed in oz-host.ts (~68).\n\nDELIVERABLE: write ONE design note to `docs/design/0087-route-repair-to-active-deb.md` (create the dir if needed) that answers, with concrete file:line evidence:\n1. OWNER MAP: every surface that spawns/handles the repair-dialogue Deb turn and every place an active Deb session is (or could be) tracked — the spawn site, the session registries (run-scoped store + liveRefs + the Oz workspace-keyed map), the dialogue state machine, the observer pane file-channel, and the tests that pin all of it.\n2. CAPABILITY CHECK (the decisive question): Does the SessionHost / adapter layer ALREADY support sending a one-shot turn (a fresh prompt) INTO an existing live pane session AND capturing its structured artifact to a known output path? Quote the exact interface/methods. If it does NOT exist, state plainly that this is MISSING INFRASTRUCTURE (not a one-line bugfix), and describe what minimal capability would be required.\n3. HOW to detect an active Deb for a workspace (visible OR hidden): given session tracking is run-scoped, spell out the concrete lookup (e.g., most-recent run for the workspace -> its `deb` session -> membership in `ctx.liveRefs`), and how 'visible' vs 'hidden' is distinguishable (or not) from daemon state.\n4. PROPOSED MECHANISM: the minimal, reversible change that detects an active Deb and routes the repair to it, with fallback to the current headless spawn when no Deb is active. Explicitly assess whether it requires editing the base observer prompt (packages/personas/base/**) so the pane Deb can handle a repair request and emit the DebRepairResponse contract — and flag that as ADR-gated/ships-everywhere if so. Confirm it does NOT reverse ADR-0036 or ADR-0041 (Oscar-Deb only, never Bob; one commit spine; not a run rescue).\n5. TEST PLAN: the specific test(s) to add (file + assertion) proving an active Deb is reused instead of a new headless Deb being spawned, plus the fallback case.\n\nACCEPTANCE: the note exists at that path, every code claim cites file:line, and it gives a clear yes/no on the capability-check question (#2). MUST NOT: change any code outside docs/**; do not implement the fix in this atom; do not weaken any existing test or guard. Write scope: docs/** only."}}
